editorialSummary.text: Chain providing office & packaging supplies, plus a variety of services such as shipping & printing.

originalText.text:
Hate to write this review, but.....

I’ve been a loyal customer at this local FedEx for over 6 years, and it used to be a place I genuinely enjoyed going to. However, the recent decline in the quality of service and the noticeable shift in employee attitude have left me with no choice but to consider alternative shipping options.

In the past, FedEx was my go-to, but it seems like their commitment to customer satisfaction has dwindled over time. The friendly and helpful vibe I once encountered have been replaced by an attitude that is far from welcoming.

Thankfully there's a UPS store just one block away, and my recent experiences there have been a breath of fresh air. The UPS employees seem genuinely interested in providing a high level of service and assistance. It's clear that they understand that they are in the business of selling a product and service, something customers pay for.

The main reason for this low rating is the unfortunate fact that a few employees at this local FedEx location have tarnished the overall reputation of the branch. While there are still a few who maintain a customer-centric approach, they are outnumbered by those who seem disinterested, rude, and unwilling to go the extra mile to assist customers.

@fedex It's disheartening to see such a decline in service quality at a company I once trusted. I'm disappointed to say that I'll be taking my business elsewhere, to a place where I feel my money is well-spent and my needs as a customer are genuinely appreciated.

@FedEx, it's time to reevaluate your customer service standards and ensure that all your employees understand the importance of providing courteous, helpful service to your paying customers. Until then, I'll be shipping my packages with a competitor who values my business and offers the service paying customers deserve.
